context.description:
The `ProtobufParse` operator takes in a serialized Protobuf message and creates a tuple of the type generated by the `spl-schema-from-protobuf` script.
The input must contain a blob field contained a single serialized Protobuf message.
The output is the generated type from the schema creation script.

The `dataAttribute` parameter takes in a field name on the input stream of blob data type, which contains a single serialized Protobuf message.
The `protoMessage` parameter takes in the fully-qualified message name in the Protobuf schema (my.package.MyMessage).
The `protoDirectory` parameter takes in the path (relative to application directory or absolute) to the directory containing the Protobuf files.
The `protoRootFile` parameter takes in the path (relative to the `protoDirectory`) for the root Protobuf file to be processed. The operator will also include any
files imported from this root file.

+ Examples

# Examples

    stream<my.package::MyMessage_pb> myMessages = ProtobufParse(serializedRecords) {
        param
            dataAttribute: attributeName;
            protoMessage: "my.package.MyMessage";
            protoDirectory: "path/to/protobuf/files";
            protoRootFile: "nested/path/MyMessage.proto";
    }
